@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Installation"

@{b}Installation automaticly:@{ub}

  You can install @{b}ARTM@{ub} automaticly with the C= Installer. In archive
ARTM is an installer script.

@{b}Installation by your fingers:@{ub}

  The installation is very easy. @{b}ARTM@{ub} is only one program, so you can 
copy @{b}ARTM@{ub} with the copy command @{b}copy ARTM path/ARTM@{ub} in your favorite
directory. Copy the .doc files with the copy command in your favorite 
directoy too. The @{b}ARTM.guide@{ub} file should you copy to @{b}LOCALE:HELP/@{ub}.

  copy ARTM.guid SYS:LOCALE/HELP/ARTM.guide

  assign HELP: SYS:LOCAL/HELP

@{b}Following files are in archiv ARTM:@{ub}

  ARTM
  ARTM.info
  Install_ARTM
  Install_ARTM.info
  german.doc/artm.guide
  german.doc/artm.guide.info
  german.doc/artm.dok
  german.doc/artm.dok.info
  german.doc/artm.history
  german.doc/artm.history.info
  english.doc/artm.guide
  english.doc/artm.guide.info
  english.doc/artm.doc
  english.doc/artm.doc.info
  english.doc/artm.history
  english.doc/artm.history.info

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Programmstart"

@{b}Programstart from Shell:@{ub}

          
  Type  ARTM [opt]

  and ARTM will open on the WB Screen

  there are many options available:

     -q            Will bring up ARTM in its inconified form in
                   the upper right hand corner.

     -poutputpath  say where ARTM should be store his output.
                   Possible are all devices prt: ram:file.

     -ix/y         Will bring up the ARTM window in its full size,
                   but when iconified the icon will be located at
                   x and y position.

     -wx/y         Start ARTM as WB Fenster, x/y is the left upper
                   point from ARTM-Window. Should the difference from
                   x/y to the right screenside lower than 640 Pixel
                   ARTM will start at the left upper corner.

     -hx           Start ARTM as WB window, x=window.height. Is the
                   screen shorter than x ARTM-Window.Height = 168.


@{b}Programmstart from WorkBench:@{ub}


  Simply double click the ARTM icon and the ARTM window will
  open on the Workbenchscreen

  The options mentioned above can be used as Tooltype.

     START=WINDOW|ICON
     ICON_POS=x/y
     OUTPUT_PATH=RAM:ARTM.output
     WINDOWHEIGHT=280
     WINDOW_POS=70/16

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================
@Node "Tastaturbelegung"

@{b}Keyboardcodes are supported in ARTM:@{ub}

  this version of ARTM support only 3 keycodes. In one of the next versiones
all functiones should be useable over the keyboard.

@{b}Followed keyboardcodes are supported:@{ub}

  ESC      finished ARTM
  HELP     the ARTM.GUIDE pop up and show you the actuel function help
           (see function @{"Help" link "Hilfe"})

@{b}ARTM requester known followed keyboardcodes:@{ub}

  ESC      cancel the function is like CANCEL
  RETURN   execute the function is like OK

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Hilfe"

@{b}The Helpfunction in ARTM:@{ub}

  an extensive help is available in ARTM. After hitting @{b}helpkey@{ub}, ARTM.guide
pops up and the last selected function help will be show you. The
@{b}amigaguide.librarie@{ub} in your @{b}Libs:@{ub} directory is required. Allso ARTM.guide
must be correct installed. (see @{"Installation" link "Installation"})

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Funktionen"

@{b}Followed functiones are implemented:@{ub}

   @{"Tasks" link "Tasks"}		      list all running tasks
   @{"Windows" link "Windows"}		      list all screens and windows
   @{"Libraries" link "Libraries"}		      list all open libraries
   @{"Devices" link "Devices"}		      list all open devices
   @{"Resources" link "Resources"}		      list all Resources
   @{"Ports" link "Ports"}		      list all open ports
   @{"Residents" link "Residents"}		      list all resident programs
   @{"Interrupts" link "Interrupts"}		      list all interrupts
   @{"Vectors" link "Vectors"}		      list the value from systemectors
   @{"Memory" link "Memory"}		      list all memorybanks
   @{"Mount" link "Mount"}		      list all mounted devices
   @{"Assign" link "Assign"}		      list all assigned devices
   @{"Locks" link "Locks"}		      list all locks
   @{"Fonts" link "Fonts"}		      list all disk- and romfonts
   @{"Hardware" link "Hardware"}		      show the most significant hardware things
   @{"Resident Cmds" link "Res_Cmds"}	      list all residente programs
   @{"Semaphoren" link "Semaphoren"}		      list all semaphores
   @{"Monitor" link "Monitor"}		      a litle memory-monitor readonly
   @{"Last Alert" link "Last Alert"}		      show the last alert number and address

   @{"zz" link "zz"}		              the ARTM-Window goes iconify
   @{" I " link " I "}		              show the AboutRequester
   @{"Disksymbol" link "Disksymbol"}		      spool datas to file or prt:

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Aktionen"

@{b}Followed aktiones are possible:@{ub}


   @{"Remove" link "Remove"}		      remove tasks etc. from a list
   @{"Close" link "Close"}		      close windows or screens
   @{"Relase" link "Release"}		      released semaphores
   @{"Clear" link "Clear"}		      cleared vectors
   @{"Freeze" link "Freeze"}		      freeze a runnig task
   @{"Activate" link "Freeze"}		      the opposite from freeze
   @{"Priority" link "Priority"}		      change priorities from tasks etc.
   @{"Unlock" link "Unlock"}		      unlocked fieles, Icons etc.
   @{"More" link "More"}	                      show the structur from selected funktion
   @{"Break" link "Break"}		      send CTRL C/D/E/F to a selected task
   @{"Signal" link "Signal"}		      send signals to a task

   @{"Address" link "Monitor_acts"}		      search a addresse in function monitor
   @{"Forward" link "Monitor_acts"}		      side forward in functin Monitor
   @{"Backward" link "Monitor_acts"}		      side backward in functin Monitor
   @{"Search" link "Monitor_acts"}		      search a ASCII string in functin Monitor

   @{"Cancel" link "Cancel"}		      switch last gadget-row from function to action

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Tasks"

@{b}Tasks:@{ub}

  is default at start of ARTM and lists all tasks in your Amiga. You select
a task with a mouseklick on the requested entry. Now you can choose any
action.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"}, @{"Priority" link "Priority"}, @{"Freeze" link "Freeze"}, @{"Activate" link "Freeze"}, @{"More" link "More"}, @{"Break" link "Break"} and @{"Signal" link "Signal"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

Address, Priority, Signals, State, Code, Type, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Pri Stack  Signals  State Code Type     Name                  
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
003f96f0    0  4094  00000010 run   ET-- process  ARTM                  
002f1cc0    0  2998  80000000 wait  ET-- process  « ConClip »           

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Windows"

@{b}Windows:@{ub}

  lists all open screens and windows. Screens are in color 3 windows are
in color 2. In a standart palette WB2.0 coler 3 ar white and coler 2 is
black. Select a window or screen by clicking on it and than select any
followed action. 


@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Close" link "Close"} and @{"More" link "More"}.

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

Address, Position, Size, Flags, IDCMP ( nur bei Windows ), Title.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address    Pos    Size   Flags    IDCMP    Title                        
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
002c1428   0,0   708,512 00004611          Workbench Screen             
003da88c  68,16  640,283 2800300f 00400670 AMIGA RealTime Monitor V2.0 Beta

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Libraries"

@{b}Libraries:@{ub}

  lists all Libraries. By click on any item, you can do any actions with
the selected library. When you remove a library (be carefull the OpenCount
must be NULL) you can do this with action close.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"}, @{"Priority" link "Priority"}, and @{"Close" link "Close"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

Address, Type, Priority, OpenCount, Version (setzt sich zusammen aus
Version & Revision), Negsize, Possize, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Type      Pri OpenC Version    Neg   Pos  Name                
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
002801b0  library     0   25  40.1       296    48  utility.library     
00283d74  library     0    1  40.24     1076   544  graphics.library    

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Devices"

@{b}Devices:@{ub}

  lists all devices. Select any item to do any action with it. Before you 
remove a device be sure that it's closed.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"} and @{"Priority" link "Priority"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

Address, Type, Priority, OpenCount, Version (consist of version & revision),
Negsize, Possize, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Type      Pri OpenC Version    Neg   Pos  Name                
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00286e74  device      0    1  40.1        36   338  gameport.device     
0028700c  device      0   19  39.4        68   380  timer.device        

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Resources"

@{b}Resources:@{ub}

  lists all resources. By click on any item, you can do any actions with
the selected resource.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"} and @{"Priority" link "Priority"}
            
@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Type, Priority, OpenCount, Version (consist of version & revision),
Negsize, Possize, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Type      Pri OpenC Version     Neg   Pos  Name               
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00280254  resource    0     0   37.0       20    42  potgo.resource     
002802b8  resource    0     0    0.0       24   136  ciaa.resource      

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Ports"

@{b}Ports:@{ub}

  shows all ports and the name of its task. IDCMP_Ports are owned by a
window. Be @{b}sure@{ub} that the process is killed when you remove his port,
else the @{b}ALERT@{ub} visit you.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"}
            
@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, PortName, Type, SigBit, Flags, TaskName.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Pri Portname            Type    SigBit Flags   TaskName       
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00300d50    0 fBlanker            msgport   30   signal  fBlanker       
0032b864    0 REXX                msgport   31   signal  RexxMaster     

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================
  
@Node "Residents"

@{b}Residents:@{ub}

  lists all residents in your Amiga. Residents which were added by the
KickTagPtr (i.e. a virus or RAD:) will be diplayed in color 3 and if the
residents are in the ResModules-table too, they will be displayed in
color 3.

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Type, Priority, Version, Flags, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Type      Pri Vers Flags    Name                              
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
002036d0  library   110   40 00000002 expansion.library                 
002000b6  library   105   40 00000002 exec.library                      

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Interrupts"

@{b}Interrupts:@{ub}

  shows all interrupts in your Amiga. It's only allowed to @{b}remove@{ub} an
interrupt controled by a server.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"}
            
@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Data, Code, Priority, Type, Nr., InterruptName, Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address  Data     Code     Pri Type      Ctrl Nr IntrName   Name        
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00283882 00283834 0021507c   0 unknown   hand  1 Disk Block disk.resource
002802e2 002802b8 0020e6ba 120 interrupt serv  3 CIA-A      ciaa.resource

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Vectors"

@{b}Vectors:@{ub}

  show vectors, i.e. Cool-, Cold,- WarmCapture and Kickpointers. It's help-
ful when searching for Viruses, but remember that the RAD: device in Kick 1.3
uses the KickTagPtr. Use function @{b}clear@{ub} to set any Vector to NULL. If you
close KickMemPtr, KickTagPtr or KickCheckSum, all of these three would be
set to NULL. Should the KickTagPtr point to a resident table, you get the
Address & Name from this residents. Note, that only the first item of the
table would be displayed. If you want to see the others, select function
Residents. The residents of the KickTagPtrtable would be displayed colored.
(see above).

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Clear" link "Clear"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, VectorName und Content,Should the KickTagPtr point to a resident
table, you get the Address & Name from this residents.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address    Content    Name             Address  Name                    
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
0028083a   00000000   ColdCapture                                       
0028083e   00000000   CoolCapture                                       
00280842   00000000   WarmCapture                                       
00280a32   00000000   KickMemPtr                                        
00280a36   00000000   KickTagPtr                                        
00280a3a   00000000   KickCheckSum                                      

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Memory"

@{b}Memory:@{ub}

  show the memory in chip, fast and expansion ram (like avail). Function
@{b}priority@{ub} changs the priority. If you select the memory (chip or fast) and
klick @{b}more@{ub} then ARTM will show you the memoryfragmention.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Priority" link "Priority"} and @{"More" link "More"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Priority, Attribute, Lower, Upper, Maximum, in Use, Free,
Largest, Name and in the next colum the totals.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Pri Lower    Upper   Maximum In-Use   Free Largest Name       
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00280000    0 00280020 00600000  3583k  1692k  1891k   1853k expansion mem
00000400  -10 00000420 00100000  1022k   237k   785k    763k chip memory

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

