@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Fonts"

@{b}Fonts:@{ub}

  list all loaded fonts, in KickRom too. With @{b}remove@{ub} you can remove the
selected Font. If you finish a program that use the font (Count = NULL),
the system should release the requested memory.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Count, YSize, XSize, Style, Flgs, LoChar, HiChar und Name.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Cnt    Y    X Style Flags LoChar HiChar Type Name             
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00286cf8   25    8    8    00    41     32    255 ROM  topaz.font       
00286ca8    3    9   10    08    49     32    255 ROM  topaz.font       
002df3ea    9    8    8    00    42     32    255 disk pearl.font       

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Hardware"

@{b}Hardware:@{ub}

  list all installed autoconfig-boards (ExpansionBase) @{b}ARTM@{ub} will show you
which processor and mathcoprocessor is in your Amiga. In addition @{b}ARTM@{ub}
indicate the new ECS-Chips Fat Agnus or Fat Denise (PAL or NTSC) or normal
Agnus and Denise. Now @{b}ARTM@{ub} will detect the new AA Chipset. At last you
can see the state from the CPU 68020 and up, and the used Kickstart (from
ROM or kickfile) and Workbench revision. 

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Boardadr, Boardsize, Slotadr, Slotsize, Driver, Product, Type,
Manufacturer und Board.

@{u}My Hardware as example:@{uu}

Address  Boardadr Bo.Size  Slotadr Ssize Driver Prod Type Manuf Boardname
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00000420 00200000  2048kB 00000020    32     no   81  230   514 A2630   
00000468 00e90000    64kB 000000e9     1    yes   11  209  2017 GVP-II HD
000004b0 00400000  2048kB 00000040    32     no   10  230  2017 GVPMemory
                                                                        
Processor ............................... 68030                         
Math CoProcessor......................... 68882                         
MMU ..................................... 68030 (OFF)                   
DMA CustomChip .......................... ECS Agnus (PAL)               
Graphic CustomChip ...................... Normal Denise                 
CPU Instruction Cache ................... ON                            
CPU Instruction Burst ................... ON                            
CPU Data Cache .......................... ON                            
CPU Data Burst .......................... ON                           
Kickstart Rom ........................... 2.04                          
Rom Kickstart Version  .................. 37.175                        
Used Kickstart Version .................. 37.175                         
Workbench Version ....................... 38.12                         

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Res_Cmds"

@{b}Resident Cmds:@{ub}

  list all Residents commands in the ROM and all programs they are made 
resident with @{b}resident programm pure@{ub} include DataHunks.

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Name, ROM INTERN,

  and if the program is made resident with @{b}resident programm pure@{ub} you will
see the Lower, Upper und Size from the DataHunks.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Name                                                                    
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
ls                                                                      
Hunks:                                                                  
Lower     Upper         Size                                            
----------------------------                                            
004351c0  00438324     12652                                            
004046b0  0040530c      3172                                            
total:                 15824                                            
                                                                        
Alias                ROM INTERN                                         
Ask                  ROM INTERN                                         
CD                   ROM INTERN                                         

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Semaphoren"

@{b}Semaphoren:@{ub}

  show all Semaphores from AmigaDos. With @{b}remove@{ub} you can remove the
selected Semaphore but before, the Semaphore will automaticly be released.
With @{b}release@{ub} you can release any Semaphores.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Remove" link "Remove"} and @{"Release" link "Release"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Priority, NestCount, WaitQueue, Name, OwnerTask.

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address   Pri  Nest Queue  Name                  OwnerTask              
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
002d775c    0    0    -1   « IPrefs »            NO_OWNER_TASK          
0038ae74 -100    0    -1   Alert Patch           NO_OWNER_TASK          

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Monitor"

@{b}Monitor:@{ub}

  is a little memorymonitor and shows the whole memory. The memory will be
loaded 100 lines in the ARTM stringgadget. With @{b}forward@{ub} and @{b}backward@{ub} you
can view the next or previous 100 records. A click on @{b}address@{ub} will bring
up a requester, type an address in it and the Monitor list the value from
memory and the next 100 records from the address. By klick on @{b}search@{ub} a
requester pop up. Fill in an ASCII string and klick on @{b}return@{ub}. If ARTM
found the string it will be display on top and the next 100 lines.

@{b}These are possibile actions:@{ub}

  @{"Forward" link "Monitor_acts"}, @{"Backward" link "Monitor_acts"}, @{"Address" link "Monitor_acts"} and @{"Search" link "Monitor_acts"}

@{b}These informationes are displayed:@{ub}

  Address, Bytes(Hex), Bytes(ASCII)

@{u}Example:@{uu}

Address     Bytes(Hex)                 Bytes(ASCII)                     
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00200000    11 16 4e f9 00 20 00 d2    . . N ů .   . Ň                  
00200008    00 00 ff ff 00 28 00 3e    . . ˙ ˙ . ( . >                  
00200010    00 28 00 0a ff ff ff ff    . ( . . ˙ ˙ ˙ ˙                  
00200018    00 41 4d 49 47 41 20 52    . A M I G A   R                  
00200020    4f 4d 20 4f 70 65 72 61    O M   O p e r a                  
00200028    74 69 6e 67 20 53 79 73    t i n g   S y s                  
00200030    74 65 6d 20 61 6e 64 20    t e m   a n d                    
...
..
.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Last Alert"

@{b}Last Alert:@{ub}

  show the last Alertnumber and address in the comment field above the list-
view gadged.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "zz"

@{b}zz:@{ub}

  Iconify function. If you chose the zz gadget ARTM disappears and popup as
an icon. A doubleklick on this icon and ARTM will bring its Window back.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node " I "

@{b}I:@{ub}

  show the AboutRequester

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Disksymbol"

@{b}Disksymbol:@{ub}

  store all items from the current called funktion in a file or put it out
to PRT: see @{"Programstart" link "Programmstart"} option -poutputpath.          

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================
@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Priority"

@{b}Priority:@{ub}

  changes the priority of a selected function. Values may range from
-128 to 127, better use values between -10 and 10. If you change a
programpriority to 10 and up please remember important processes could
run much slower.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Tasks" link "Tasks"}		      	      list all running tasks
  @{"Libraries" link "Libraries"}		      list all open libraries
  @{"Devices" link "Devices"}		      list all open devices
  @{"Resources" link "Resources"}		      list all Resources
  @{"Ports" link "Ports"}		     	      list all open ports
  @{"Interrupts" link "Interrupts"}		      list all interrupts
  @{"Memory" link "Memory"}		      list all memorybanks

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Remove"

@{b}Remove:@{ub}

  removes selected function. Select (before remove) with a mouseclick on the
requested entry. But remember libs amd devices must be closed.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Tasks" link "Tasks"}		      list all running tasks
  @{"Libraries" link "Libraries"}		      list all open libraries
  @{"Devices" link "Devices"}		      list all open devices
  @{"Resources" link "Resources"}		      list all Resources
  @{"Ports" link "Ports"}		      list all open ports
  @{"Interrupts" link "Interrupts"}		      list all interrupts
  @{"Fonts" link "Fonts"}		      list all disk- and romfonts
  @{"Semaphoren" link "Semaphoren"}		      list all semaphores

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Close"

@{b}Close:@{ub}

  closes screens/windows and libraries. Use it as remove.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Windows" link "Windows"}		      list all screens and windows
  @{"Libraries" link "Libraries"}		      list all open libraries

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Release"

@{b}Release:@{ub}

  relase Semaphores from SignalSemaphoreList.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Semaphoren" link "Semaphoren"}		      list all semaphores

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Clear"

@{b}Clear:@{ub}

  set the SystemVectors to NULL. Use it as remove or close. Is any System-
vector not = NULL so a @{b}Virus@{ub} could be resident in your Amiga. Function
@{b}Clear@{ub} will remov him from the resident structure. After the next reset,
he is removed. Some usefull programs could be resident too Rad etc.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Vectors" link "Vectors"}		      list the value from systemectors

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Freeze"

@{b}Freeze:@{ub}

  freeze a runnig Task and removed it form the nodestructur. The frozen task-
structur is stored. You recognize it function  @{b}Task@{ub} on STATE "Frozen".
If you select a forzen task and click @{b}Activate@{ub} the task get a new live.

@{b}Activate:@{ub}

  is the counterpart from @{b}Freeze@{ub}. Show above.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Unlock"

@{b}Unlock:@{ub}

  remove a @{b}Lock@{ub} (read or write) from the list. Attention if the system know
the Lock, your Amiga will get an Alert.  

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "More"

@{b}More:@{ub}

  show detail informationes about task, process, CLI, window, screen und
memory structure. It's not ever the complete structur but the most important
things.

@{b}These functiones are supported:@{ub}

  @{"Tasks" link "Tasks"}			      list all running tasks
  @{"Windows" link "Windows"}		      list all screens and windows
  @{"Memory" link "Memory"}		      list all memorybanks

@{u}Example:@{uu}

  Klick on the requested task and then on @{b}More@{ub}. This is the result from:

@{u}Task- Process- and ComandLineInterface Structure plus Hunks from ToolManger@{uu}

Task Structure:                                                         
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
IDNestCnt:            -1                TDNestCnt:             0        
SigAlloc:       c000ffff                SigWait:        c000f000        
SigRecvd:       00000100                SigExcept:      00000000        
TrapAlloc:      00008000                TrapAble:       00000000        
ExceptData:     00000000                ExceptCode:     002033f0        
TrapData:       00000000                TrapCode:       0021678e        
SPLower:        0037ca48                SPUpper:        0037da48        
SPReg:          0037d946                                                
Switch():       00000000                Launch():       00000000        
MemEntry:       00389b16                UserData:       00000000        
Process Structure:                                                      
WindowPtr:      00000000                Title:                          
CurrentDir:     00371fa8                Path:  Amiga:                   
MsgPort:        00000000                                                
StackBase:      00389bac                StackSize:          3200        
CIS:            0036577c                COS:            003654a4        
ConsoleTask:    00000000                FileSystemTask: 00294ca4        
SegList:        00367328                SegPointer:     00000000        
PktWait:        00000000                CLI:            000d98ff        
CommandLineInterface Structure:                                         
CommandDir:     002c94a4                                                
StandardInput:  0036577c                StandardOutput: 003654a4        
CurrentInput:   0036577c                CurrentOutput:  003654a4        
