Hunks:
Lower     Upper         Size
----------------------------
0038c9e0  00396520     39752
0037b7b8  0037ca40      4752
00023378  00023408       152
total:                 44656

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Break"

@{b}Break:@{ub}

  cancel a runnig Task. It will be set Control D/E/F/C

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Signal"

@{b}Signal:@{ub}

  A requester pops up where you can change the value from tc_SigAlloc. Then
Dosfunction @{b}Signal@{ub} get it back.

 See function @{"Break" link "Break"}

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Cancel"

@{b}Cancel:@{ub}

  switch the last gadgetrow from @{b}action@{ub} (color 4) back to @{b}function@{ub} (color 2).
So function monitor, Hardware etc. are visible.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Monitor_acts"

@{b}Address:@{ub}

  Pop up a little Requester. Put here your faworite address. Function
Monitor search the address and will display it in the first item plus the
next 100 rows.

@{b}Forward:@{ub}

  list the next 100 rows.

@{b}Backward:@{ub}

  list the previus 100 rows

@{b}Search:@{ub}

  Pop up a little Requester. Put here the searched ASCII string. Function
Monitor search the string and when it is found ARTM will display it in the
first item plus the next 100 rows.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "History"

@{b}History:@{ub}

  The program-history from @{b}ARTM@{ub} is a separated file like @{b}ARTM.History@{ub}.
The reason to not include the history in this guide is, the guid grow up
and would bo to big.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Zukunft"

@{b}Future:@{ub}

  I would like add to @{b}ARTM@{ub} some new features in the near time. Some
things go slower than I've a fulltime job too. These listed functions will be
add in one of the next versions:


  @{u}show the CPU-Usage@{uu}

  @{u}switch on- and off the CPU-Caches@{uu}

  @{u}A litle preference program instead tooltypes and shell-optiones@{uu}

  @{u}a traphandler to catch some alerts@{uu}

  @{u}specifyed otput to function @{"Last Alert" link "Last Alert"}@{uu}

  @{u}a litle AREXX port@{uu}

  @{u}a shared Library board.library for additional hardware boards@{uu}



  If you have some suggestions please let it me know.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Hinweis"

@{b}Note:@{ub}

  If you use the function hardware and have installed autoconfig-boards
(ExpansionBase). Please send me a mail and tell us the output from ARTM
(PROD, TYPE and MANUFACTRER) and also the name and Type of your expansion-
bords.

  You should ever know what you do! You could change some things in your
Amiga so, that the alert visit you. @{b}Be careful.@{ub}

  Please send bug reports and a list of features you would like to have
in the next version to the Author. The easyesd way to call the author is
E-Mail see @{"Autor" link "Author"}.

@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

